==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uncertainty
<hw>Un*cer"tain*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Uncertainties</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being uncertain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is uncertain; something
unknown.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our shepherd's case is every man's case that quits a moral
certainty for an <qex>uncertainty</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncessant</ent>⟦br⟧
